-- India cbank says easing trading rules for infra bonds will not deepen mkts
-- By Suvashree Dey Choudhury
-- Wed Aug 20, 2014 03:39AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, Aug 20 (Reuters) - Allowing the trading of bonds issued for infrastructure lending will not help deepen debt markets, newly appointed Reserve Bank of India Deputy Governor S.S. Mundra said on Wednesday.

Last month, RBI had said that trading of such bonds was not permitted. [ID:nI8N0ND05J]